The National Coordinator, Concerned Advocates for Good Governance, CAGG, Barrister Olusegun Bamgbose, Esq., has commended the President Muhammadu Buhari-led federal government for reopening banks and extending the working hours for civil servants in the country. DAILY POST reported that the Nigerian Government, earlier on Monday, ordered that banks in the country resume normal working hours. Chairman of the task force, Boss Mustapha, announced that President Buhari said the second phase of the eased lockdown would be in place for four weeks. He also ordered civil servants to work from 9 am to 2 pm Monday -Friday Reacting to the development in a chat with DAILY POST, Bamgbose said, “The ease as announced by the Federal Government is a welcome development and a big relief. “Civil servants from grade level 14 are to resume by 9am and close by 2pm. Now banks are to operate fully. This is a good one. “Our economy is in bad shape and these developments will help in reviving the economy.”